---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import EpisodeSequencePlate from "../components/EpisodeSequencePlate.astro";
import EpisodePartStructure from "../components/EpisodePartStructure.astro";
import EpisodeAnchorsIndex from "../components/EpisodeAnchorsIndex.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<Layout title="Episodes" description="The seventy-three episodes of Gravity's Rainbow, treated as a formal sequence.">
  <Nav slot="nav" />

  <Section>
    <div class="page-head reveal visible">
      <p class="eyebrow">01</p>
      <h1>The seventy-three episodes</h1>
      <div class="page-lede">
        <p>
          <em>Gravity's Rainbow</em> is treated here as a sequence of seventy-three
          formal units. This first layer shows formal scale and rhythm: order,
          part structure, word count, and paragraph count.
        </p>
        <p>
          The aim is not a table of contents. It is a reading map: the book as a
          temporal score, with expansion, compression, and part boundaries visible
          before selected public anchors attach formal rhythm to plot progression
          and motifs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <section class="plate-break reveal visible">
    <div class="plate-container">
      <figure class="episode-figure">
        <EpisodeSequencePlate />
      </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <figcaption class="plate-caption">
        Every mark is one episode in reading order. Height carries word count;
        interior ticks carry paragraph structure. The density view shifts the
        emphasis from scale to paragraph rhythm, making compact but sharply
        divided sections easier to see.
      </figcaption>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Section narrow={true}>
    <div class="prose-block reveal visible">
      <p>
        The sequence is uneven by design. Part III contains the widest spread,
        including the longest episode and several abrupt compressions. Part IV is
        shorter in episode count but ends with two large late movements. The
        plate makes those changes legible as structure before it asks what they
        mean.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <section class="plate-break reveal visible">
    <div class="plate-container">
      <figure class="episode-figure">
        <EpisodePartStructure />
      </figure>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <figcaption class="plate-caption">
        Part-level structure summarised from the same public-safe metadata. The
        movement trace preserves episode order within each part while the lower
        rule compares total word mass.
      </figcaption>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Section narrow={true}>
    <div class="anchor-block reveal visible">
      <p class="eyebrow">Episode anchors</p>
      <p>
        The anchor layer adds a small set of public interpretive labels to the
        structural score. Where a short quotation has been manually approved, it
        appears as secondary evidence beneath the site commentary.
      </p>
      <EpisodeAnchorsIndex />
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section narrow={true}>
    <div class="notes-block reveal visible">
      <p class="eyebrow">Notes</p>
      <ol class="notes-list">
        <li>
          The episode layer uses only the public-safe metadata export:
          global order, episode ID, part, part title, word count, and paragraph
          count. No source text, snippets, quotations, descriptions, or evidence
          fields are present.
        </li>
        <li>
          The imported CSV is logged in <code>data/provenance.md</code>. It is
          served from
          <a href={`${base}/data/base/episode_metadata_public.csv`}>public/data/base/episode_metadata_public.csv</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          The anchor and quote layers are served from
          <a href={`${base}/data/base/episode_anchors_public.csv`}>public/data/base/episode_anchors_public.csv</a>
          and
          <a href={`${base}/data/base/episode_anchor_quotes_public.csv`}>public/data/base/episode_anchor_quotes_public.csv</a>.
          The quote layer is sparse, manually approved, and contains no context
          windows or bulk source text.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Layout>

<style>
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .page-lede {
    max-width: var(--max-width-narrow);
  }

  .page-lede p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .plate-break {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
  }

  .plate-container {
    max-width: min(98vw, 96rem);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-lg);
  }

  .episode-figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .plate-caption {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    max-width: var(--max-width-narrow);
  }

  .prose-block p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    max-width: var(--max-width-narrow);
  }

  .anchor-block {
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .anchor-block p:not(.eyebrow) {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    max-width: var(--max-width-narrow);
  }

  .notes-block {
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  @media (max-width: 48rem) {
    .plate-container {
      max-width: 100vw;
      padding: 0 var(--space-md);
    }
  }

  .notes-list {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    padding-left: 1.5em;
    list-style: decimal;
  }

  .notes-list li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .notes-list li a {
    color: var(--color-accent-dim);
  }

  .notes-list li a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .notes-list code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
</style>
